<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-60-0630 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book deals with the cosmic magnetism in a non-mathematical way. Ituses Faraday's very powerful and highly pictorial concept of lines ofmagnetic force and their associated physical properties to explain thestructure and behavior of magnetic fields in extraterrestrial objects.Contents include: forces of nature; magnetic field of earth; solar andinterplanetary magnetic fields; magnetic fields in the solar system;stars and pulsars; and magnetic fields of the milky way and other galaxies.</TEXT></DOC>